mkdir <directory name> (to create new directory)
pwd (to get current directory)
cd <directory name> (to change the dir)
cd .. (to move one step back)
ls (to get list of files and dir)
ll (to get list files and dir with permissions and sizes)
more <file_name> (to create new file)
vi <file_name> (to edit the file)
rm -rf <file_name> (to remove the file)
rmdir <dir name> (to remove dir)
ls -al (to get dir,files,hidden files and hidden directory)
touch <file_name> (to create new file)
:wq (to save the text in the file)
:q! (to close the file without saving the text)
cat <file_name> (to show the text in the file)
